Given two genome multi-fasta files, we want to search genomeA using genomeB


## distribute the genomeA sequence:
bhaas@bhaas-lx % ~/twinscan_informant_scripts/distribute_genome_among_dirs.pl genomeA


## get a list of the accessions:

 accession_extractor.pl < genomeA > genomeA.accessions

## promer the genomes.
-first, manually run promer using a small reference contig so that the translated versions of the genome will be generated
$EGC_UTILITIES/bhaas_promer small_contig_fasta  genomeB

Now, run all the promer searches on the grid:

# generate promer coords file, filter out repeats, chain neighboring matches
~/twinscan_informant_scripts/prepare_for_blast.pl sma1.repeatmasked.genome.accessions

# extract homologous regions from other genome, create miniDB for blast searches
~/twinscan_informant_scripts/run_generate_miniDB.pl sma1.repeatmasked.genome.accessions `pwd`/sja1.repeatmasked.genome

# run tblastx
~/twinscan_informant_scripts/run_TblastX_on_grid.pl sma1.repeatmasked.genome.accessions

# generate conseq files:
~/twinscan_informant_scripts/make_conseq_files.pl sma1.repeatmasked.genome.accessions


# load conserved regions into the database:
~/twinscan_informant_scripts/load_conserved_regions_into_db.dbi sma1.repeatmasked.genome.accessions sma1 Sj_cons


# relocate the conseq files to the annotdb asmbl_id directories:
 ~/twinscan_informant_scripts/relocate_conseq_files.pl sma1.repeatmasked.genome.accessions sma1
